The University of Lagos’ convocation ceremonies, which was slated to begin on Monday, have been suspended. This was confirmed in a statement by Oladejo Azeez, the Registrar and Secretary to UNILAG’s Council, on Thursday. “The Management of the University of Lagos regrets to inform the general public that the 51st (2019) Convocation Ceremonies earlier scheduled to hold from Monday 9th to Thursday 12th March, 2020 have been postponed. “Any inconvenience occasioned by this postponement is highly regretted,” it read. UNILAG’s Vice-Chancellor, Prof. Oluwatoyin Ogundipe, had on Monday announced the schedule for the school’s 51st convocation. Ogundipe noted that 13,489 graduates would receive degrees, diplomas and certificates at the event.